which the oblique case was <i>Bacon</i>.","English and French: from Middle English, Old French <i>bacun</i>, <i>bacon</i> ‘bacon’ (a word of ancient Germanic origin, akin to   Back   3), probably a metonymic occupational name for a preparer and seller of cured pork.","History: Gilles Bacon from Normandy, France, is documented in Quebec City, QC, in 1647. — Michael Bacon from England arrived in Dedham, MA, in 1640. Nathanial Bacon, from Stratton, Cornwall, arrived in Barnstaple, MA, in 1639. Another Nathaniel Bacon (1647–76), from Friston Hall, Suffolk, emigrated to VA and settled at Curl's Neck on the James river."],"variants":[{"name":"Bagg","meanings":["English:","from Middle English <i>bagge</i> ‘bag, pack, bundle’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a maker of bags and sacks of various kinds, including wallets and purses. It might also have been used for a beggar, or for one who carried their belongings in a bag.","from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Bago</i> (<i>Bac(c)o</i>, <i>Bahho</i>), from the root <i>bag-</i> ‘to fight’ (see   Bacon   2)."]},{"name":"Back","meanings":["English (Devon, Kent, Sussex, and Norfolk): from the Middle English personal name <i>Bakke</i> (Old English <i>Bacca</i>). It is of uncertain origin, but may have been a byname in the same sense as 3.","English: nickname from Middle English <i>bakke</i> ‘bat’, of uncertain application, perhaps a nickname for a person with poor eyesight, from the expression ‘blind as a bat’.","English: from Middle English <i>bakke</i> ‘back’ (Old English <i>bæc</i>), hence a nickname for someone with a hunched back or some other noticeable peculiarity of the back or spine, or a topographic name for someone who lived on a hill or ridge, or at the rear of a settlement."]}]},{"name":"Adam","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical.  See  <b>Adam</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Adam Bacon was born about 1206, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Alice Planteine."},"et":{"about 1206–":"umbes 1206–Surnud","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1236–Female":"1236–Surnud","1206–Male":"1206–Surnud","1206":"1206","1236":"1236","about 1206":"umbes 1206","1210":"1210","about 1236":"umbes 1236","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1206–":"noin 1206–Kuollut","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1236–Female":"1236–Kuollut","1206–Male":"1206–Kuollut","1206":"1206","1236":"1236","about 1206":"noin 1206","1210":"1210","about 1236":"noin 1236","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1206–":"environ 1206–Décédé","1210–Female":"1210–Décédée","1236–Female":"1236–Décédée","1206–Male":"1206–Décédé","1206":"1206","1236":"1236","about 1206":"environ 1206","1210":"1210","about 1236":"environ 1236","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Adam Bacon est né environ 1206, à Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Alice Planteine."},"de":{"about 1206–":"um 1206–Verstorben","1210–Female":"1210–Verstorben","1236–Female":"1236–Verstorben","1206–Male":"1206–Verstorben","1206":"1206","1236":"1236","about 1206":"um 1206","1210":"1210","about 1236":"um 1236","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Adam Bacon wurde um 1206 in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mit Alice Planteine mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"about 1206–":"about 1206–Desede","1210–Female":"1210–Desede","1236–Female":"1236–Desede","1206–Male":"1206–Desede","1206":"1206","1236":"1236","about 1206":"about 1206","1210":"1210","about 1236":"about 1236","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"about 1206–":"1206 körül–elhunyt","1210–Female":"1210–elhunyt","1236–Female":"1236–elhunyt","1206–Male":"1206–elhunyt","1206":"1206","1236":"1236","about 1206":"1206 kör